talk\\text\\crw_kurodenwa_01.lxtxt-phone.TB:
Hello. I heard that I can buy cigarettes on the cheap
if I'm one of the first to call you.

Oh, so you saw our flyer.
Then let me ask—what's our slogan?
Slogan? What the hell is that?

I can't sell 'em to you if you don't know the slogan.
At least try and do a little research.
Anyway, I'm hanging up now.
(A slogan, huh? Guess I'll look it up and call back.)
Your slogan is, "No smoke, no fire."

Bingo. I'll set some aside for you at a discount.
A pack of these'll really get you worked up.
Oops, I nearly forgot. What's your name?
Name's Daito. It's a pleasure.
Welcome.
I'm Daito—from the phone call earlier.

Oh, it's you.
I've got your discounted cigarettes right here.
Thanks.

Hey, about that slogan on the flyer... I haven't been able
to make the phone call yet.
Right, the discount thing—"No smoke, no fire."

Yeah, that.
It's just that it's embarrassing to say over the phone.

I'd feel stupid saying something like that
to a person I can't even see.

So the slogan is, "No smoke, no fire."
Must be a smoke shop.
Welcome. You saw the flyer too?

Huge discount on cigarettes!
Call 1542 to preorder yours now!
A discount on cigarettes, huh? Maybe I'll give 'em a call.

Looking for this person wearing red!
Call 9708 when found!
I'm not getting through.
I'll call back later.
Hey, welcome. You saw the flyer too?
Flyer? What are you talking about?

Oh, you haven't seen the flyer. Never mind then.
What'll it be today?

If you call the number written on the flyer hung up around town,
you'll get a discount on cigarettes.

It's a limited supply though—first come, first served.
So don't wait if you want the deal.
All right.
If it's about the flyer— Oh, guess not. Welcome.

Oh, that's the flyer that guy told me about. I should call that number
when I have time.

(Right, I already bought some. They said the deal was limited
to one per customer, so there's no point in calling them again.)
Then you must have seen the flyer. I'll set some aside for you at a discount.
Remember, it's one per customer. You better not call over and over again.
Oops, I nearly forgot. What's your name?
Name's Daito. It's a pleasure.
Ah, it's you. The deal is limited to one per customer.
Right, I understand.

talk\\text\\crw_kurodenwa_02.lxtxt-phone.TB:
A missing person, huh?
Guess it wouldn't hurt to remember what he looks like.
What? You need something from me?
Nah, it's just that your clothes are... pretty unique.

Y-Yeah?
Well if you don't need anything else, I'll be going.

(With those clothes, that has to be the missing guy.
I should call that number when I have some time.)

Looks like it's the right number, but no answer.
I still haven't found the guy,
so maybe I should call again if I see him.
Hello. I just saw the person you were looking for.
You found my man!?
I did.
Where did you see him!?
I saw him wandering around Minami.
(She sure sounds angry...)
Thank you so much! I promise I'll reward you for this!
...And she hung up.

(Maybe I stuck my nose where I shouldn't have...
I should check things out in town later.)
Looks like you found him in one piece.
Thank you so much—you were a huge help!
This was none of your business...
What was that!?
Oh, uh nothing...

I'm sorry that I was so rude on the phone!
I really, really appreciate your help!
Well, I'm just glad you found him.
Call 9708 if you find the missing person, right?

Just like the poster said, his outfit was distinctive, to say the least...
Did he really not want to be found?
I'm in a hurry—let's do this later!
Seriously!? You're such a—
Yes, yes... You're right—it's just as you say.
(Maybe I should have minded my own business...)

Listen, I wanna take a photo, so do you mind waiting a bit?
I'll even pay you, so just sit tight while I get my camera.
Uh... Okay? I guess I'll just wait here for you then.
(I should make that call while I got him waiting.)

I got him waiting around the main street in Minami. He won't be here
for long, so you better get here quick.

talk\\text\\crw_minigame_chinchiro.lxtxt.TB: Hey! You're cheating, aren't you!? Those dice throws are real fishy!
If you're cheating, then that means I didn't lose! Give me back my money!
Urgh, I'm sorry. To be honest, I didn't actually think that you were cheating...

I lose in a game and in a fight... I'm a damn idiot.
Lemme pay you what I owe. Sorry for accusing you...
This is what happens to cheaters!
Was this guy actually even cheating...?
Oh! Feelin' up to a game of dice?
I'll take the the winnings from the bet. Consider it an inconvenience fee.

talk\\text\\crw_mission_001.lxtxt-daito_.TB: Can't you see you're upsetting her? Let her go.

talk\\text\\crw_mission_001.lxtxt-chinpi.TB: Whoa, what the hell was that for!?

talk\\text\\crw_mission_001.lxtxt-yuujo_.TB: Yes, thank you so much for helping me!
Thank you so much for saving me! You're very strong.

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-yakuza.TB: Huh? Don't go sticking your nose where it doesn't belong!

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-daito_.TB: And I'm saying you're pissing me off.

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-yakuza.TB:
Oh yeah? Well now I changed my mind.
I'll kick your ass first!

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-daito_.TB:
You didn't hear me?
I said to knock that shit off.

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-yakuza.TB:
Hah! Bold words there! I'll just beat you up
so you can't say them again!

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-chouni.TB:
You really saved me!
How can I ever repay you?

talk\\text\\crw_mission_002.lxtxt-daito_.TB: Don't worry about it. I'm just glad you're okay.

talk\\text\\crw_mission_003.lxtxt-yuujo_.TB: Great! Let's have some fun today.
Hehe. That makes me so happy!
Yay! We'll have a lot of fun, right?
Aw. Just for a bit, okay?
So you don't wanna have fun with me?

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_kokura_u.TB: I recommend anything on the menu!
Oh man, you really got your ass handed to you!

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_kokura_t.TB: Our stuff is top of the line!
Oh man, you really got your ass handed to you!

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_kokura_k.TB: You should take it easy on the fighting...

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_minami_s.TB: I got some nice stuff here!
Wow, you were really going wild there.

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_minami_y.TB: If you're just browsing, then get lost.
With all that crap you're carrying, I doubt you can take anything else.
You don't got the money, kid.

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_kokura_d.TB: Okay, I'll have to come back...
(No response... I guess that wasn't the slogan?)

talk\\text\\crw_shop.lxtxt-shop_kokura_y.TB: Come on, you think I'm stupid?
It's my first time for something like THAT!
Wow, mister! You sure are good at shogi!

talk\\text\\crw_show_01.lxtxt-crw_show_a.TB:
So you're Daito. I've heard about you.
I'll cut to the chase: I want my daughter to perform on stage.

You make it happen, and I foresee good things in your future.
I've got some pull in this town.

Now go on and talk to her. Her name's Haruko,
she's outside the house. I'm counting on you.

Great work. That was an outstanding performance.
Both my daughter and I thank you from the bottom of our hearts.

Here's your reward. Use it however you see fit.
Good luck out there, kid, I'm pulling for you.

(It's the request I took on from Iwanaga...
Gotta include his daughter Haruko in the show.)

(It's the request I took on from the Theater Owner.
What to do?)
(Should I draft the gig proposal with this?)

We allow booking the entire venue.
Show me a proposal if you're interested.
Obtained permission to use Venue 1.

I can't let you book the entire
venue without seeing a proposal.
All right. We can work with these terms. Now, the money.

The terms are fine, but you're short on funds.
Come back when you have the amount listed in the proposal.
(I should draft a proposal before I come back...)

You must be the foreigner I've heard about.
You gotta help me, I'm at my wits' end here.

The military band we booked for tonight
suddenly backed out, leaving me with
200 people who still expect a show.

I'll give you a discount on the rental fee,
just make it good. I'm counting on you.
Obtained permission to use Venue 2.

For this performance request, the total number
of audience members will be fixed at 200
regardless of the performer's popularity.

You might be light on business contacts in this town, huh?
Let me introduce you to some sidemen I know.

Obtained telephone numbers for Pianist 1,
Pianist 2, Drummer 1, Saxophonist 1, and Bassist 1.

Bring a proposal by if you think you can 
make a show in this hall happen.
All right, the hall's all yours.

The terms are fine, but you're short on funds.
Come back when you have the amount listed in the proposal.
(I need to draft a proposal before I come back...)

Daito, I presume? You must have spoken to my father already.
At present, I am attending a school for music.

I aspire to be a primary school choir instructor,
and thus wish to gain experience singing in public.
So I won't charge a performance fee.

And if I may... The newer foreign genres are my forte.
I would be delighted if the program included these.
You can now cast Iwanaga Haruko in shows.
I look forward to working with you.

Daito-san, we meet again.
As always, I'm still in a slump.

If only I had something new, a novel idea,
I could do some arranging on a record for you.
Works for me. Let's put our heads together.
No... I can't think of anything.
I've got it.... What about this? Take a listen.

It feels like the fog in my mind has lifted. You have my thanks.
 Please play this piece to your heart's content.
Obtained Program 1 Arrangement A.

I want to concentrate on composing now.
But I can introduce you to my brother.
He charges a fee, but he's a talented pianist.
His name is Ichiro. I'll give you his telephone number.
Obtained telephone number for Pianist 3.

You you want me to make some music,
you gotta bring some ideas to the table with me.

You got a good vibe, I feel it just talking to you.
So how 'bout it?

Let's see here...
You seen anything interesting in town lately?
Tell me what you got from that.

Hmm. Nothing comes to mind.
Feel like we're close, though...
I think we've done it. Let me note that out real quick.
Hahaha. I didn't think the arrangement'd turn out this well.
Obtained Program 1 Arrangement B.

I hope this makes it into lots of your shows.
I'm glad we composed it. See you around.
I've been waiting. Now let's put on the best show ever.
Call me if you ever need a male vocalist.
You can now cast Performer 2 in shows.
Looking forward to working with you.

There's a flyer that reads,
"Experienced drummer and taiko player seeking work",
along with their history and telephone number.
(Maybe I can enlist them as a show performer.)
Obtained telephone number for Drummer 2.

Hey Mr. Foreigner, you host music performances, don't you?
Would you consider couple relatives of mine for use in your shows?

They're a husband-wife duo, drums and saxophone.
Here's their telephone number.
Obtained telephone number for Drummer 3 and Saxophonist 2.
Hey... Could you get me some water...?
Dammit...
M-Much obliged. I owe you one.
Name's Suzuki. Onstage, I'm a saxophonist, but off it... I'm just a lousy drunk, as you can see.

Let me know if I can return this favor sometime.
Though, blowin' the horn's about the only thing I can do.
Obtained telephone number for Saxophonist 3.

This café's not hurting for customers, but 
believe it or not, you can rent the place out.

I see there's a piano. Do they allow
singing and other instruments?

Indeed. You can do parties and recitals as well.
Try speaking to the manager if you're interested.
Hello. How can I help you?
Enough with the jokes, please.

An offer? Very well...
What sort of show does it entail?

I see. That's fine. I'll require my performance fee
prior to the show's start.
Goodbye.
You can now extend an offer to pianists.
You can now extend an offer to drummers.
You can now extend an offer to saxophonists.
You can now extend an offer to bassists.
Hello, hello. What is it?
You can cut the jokes.
An offer? All right... What sort of show?
Hm. Okay. You can give me my fee before the show starts.
Bye now.

(That show wasn't as lively as I'd like...
I should think take a moment to think about why.)
(That show was pretty decent. Let's keep it up.)
(That show was perfect, I wouldn't change anything about it.)
(This musician has already agreed to perform...)
Hope it works out with my brother.
(What should I do...)
(Maybe I'll dig some music in town to find some ideas...)

While I'm at it, I'll introduce you to some bassist
friends of mine. They've been dying for some work.
(Which proposal do I want to draw up...?)

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB: Hey, Daito. Got a minute?
Tch. C'mon, man.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: What's going on?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB: We've had a thief around here lately.

I can't speak too loudly on it, but I guess some
of the Yashima Family money was stolen, too.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: What?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
That's where you come in.
I need you find him and get the money back.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Don't you think you should go to police instead?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
Are you stupid? If word gets out that the Yashima Family went
running off to the cops, our reputation would hit the gutter.

Not to mention, Aniki still doesn't know anything's
been stolen. I'm planning to keep it that way.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
So get the money back before he finds out,
and act like it never happened, is that it?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB: Bingo. You're a smart kid, you know that?
You pull this off, and I'll even give you a little allowance. Deal?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: ...All right, fine.

First off, what's this thief look like?
Any ideas where he might be?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB: Not a clue.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Huh?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
If we knew that we'd have caught 'em already.
It'll be up to you to play detective and find out.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
(Gimme a break. Guy gets the Family's money stolen,
but can't be bothered to get it back himself.)

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
The owner of the café's a bit of a rumormonger. A rich one at that.
He's also pretty well-known around here, so you might start with him.

Anyway, it's in your hands.
Come find me when you get the money.
Oh, one more thing.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Hm? What's that?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
About that thief. Do whatever you gotta do, even if that
means killin' the creep. Lowlifes like him aren't worth shit.

But if you do put him six feet under,
just empty his pockets first, all right?
Again, I'll leave all that up to you. See ya.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (Okay, let's see what this café owner has to say.)
Hey, you got a second?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: Hm? Can I help you?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Word is some thief's been robbing the rich folks
around here. You hear anything about that?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
A thief, huh? Well, I've been known to learn
a thing or two, running this place.
That is to say, yes, I know all about it.
I even know who their next target is.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: You do...!?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: I'll tell ya, though, I don't think you should meddle.

The thefts are happening, but they're not
done alone. This is a team effort.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: So it's a band of thieves.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
If ever there was one. Catching them in the act wouldn't be the end of it,
and there's a good chance they'd come after you next.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
(This'll be tricker than I thought... Still, the Family's
money was taken. I can't just back down.)

Actually, I figured I in was for a fight. You see,
there's something I need to get back from them.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Is that right? Ah, it's just that I would feel terrible if
something happened on account of me telling you...

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: You gonna help me or not!?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Now that I get a look at you, you seem like you know
how to hold your own. I'll bet you can fight, too.
Here's what I'll do.

I got a troublesome customer who's racked up a pretty
good tab here, and he's about due here for another meal.

Problem is, he goes on a rampage just about any time I ask him to pay up.
As you might imagine, my patience has run pretty thin.

If you can help me chase the guy off for good,
I'll tell you what you want to know.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Right, so what you're really saying
is I'm outta luck unless I help you.

(The owner said he'll get me the info if I take out this guy with
the tab. A little round about, but it'll get me what I want.)
(I'll talk to the owner once I'm ready.)

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: Oh? Decided to help me out after all, did you?
If you can do that, I'll give you all the information you need.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: I'm in. Let's get this guy outta here.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Haha, I appreciate the confidence.
Right then, we'll take him outside.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Wait, huh? Did you just say "we"?
You're gonna fight too?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
I may not look it now, but I had quite the wild streak
when I was younger. It hasn't left me just yet.

To that end, don't worry. If you get into
a bind, I'll step in to help you out.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Sure. Sounds good to me.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: Good, then follow me.
Ready when you are.
Shall we, then?
...There he is. That's him there.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-gouman_tuke.TB:
Hey there, pops.
I'm back for another meal.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: And I appreciate you coming.

However, before you sit down, perhaps
you'll pay off the tab you've accrued?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-gouman_tuke.TB:
What? C'mon, just put it on my tab again.
I'm hungry as shit, so don't test me.
You wouldn't want any trouble around here, would you?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Hey, back off! You're really gonna threaten a meal out of him?
Maybe have some respect for yourself and pay up, huh?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-gouman_tuke.TB: ...Ah, I get it. You got yourself a bouncer, huh?

How 'bout this, then? If I can knock this little jerk
out cold, I get free food whenever I want.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
You what...? I'm sorry, no.
I'm afraid I'll have to decline.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-gouman_tuke.TB:
Ah, shut up! By the time I'm done here,
you'll practically be begging to cook for me!

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Right. Leave what you owe, and get lost.
And don't lemme catch you comin' back, got it?

If that wasn't enough, I'll gladly beat your ass again.
I'm sure we both have a few more rounds in us.
How's it look? Will it cover his tab?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Yes. In fact, it does seem a bit more than he owed,
but I'll consider it an inconvenience fee.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Glad it worked out, then.
Now, you remember what you promised?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Of course. I'll cook you up some
Napolitan right away. Sound good?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Some what!? The hell are you talking about?
You said you'd tell me where the thieves are!

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Hahaha, I'm just joking. You've more than proven
yourself, so I've no qualms getting you involved.
I'll take you there myself. Follow me.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Hang on. You're coming too?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
I am. My place also was hit by them, and as we discussed
earlier, this is a "band" of thieves, not some pickpocket.

It would've been foolish to take them on by myself,
but with you I feel like I have a shot.
Which reminds me, I never asked your name.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: ...It's Daito.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: Well then, Daito-san. Shall we?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Yeah.

Wanted to ask: how come you know so much about
these thieves? You got a friend in the police?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
It takes one to know one, as they say.
All kinds of information passes through my place.

I'm willing to bet if you became a regular,
you'd get to know this city pretty fast.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Maybe you're right, but, uh...
You sure you're not just after my money?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: Haha. I might be.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Also, a little late to ask, I guess, but is this really the best time
to look for these guys? Thought thieves come out at night.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
That's exactly why they strike during the day.
People are usually more careful after dark.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Oh, yeah? Well, if you're so sure about that,
how come your place got hit, then?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
They waited for the exact moment I had to step out for supplies...
Didn't touch the money, just the food.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Huh. Must be pretty good about scouting ahead.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
And then some. To my point, there's evidence they've been
scouting that house there. They could hit the place at any moment.

What's more, there's a strange rumor going around about them.
Apparently, the money they steal goes to—
Ah, speak of the devil. There's one now.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: He's not getting away! Time to move!

Finally got you, you rat! You're gonna give back all
the money you stole from the Yashima Family!

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_boss_.TB: Hey, c'mon! Lend me a hand here!

Nothing against you, kid, but I can't let you walk away from this.
This town'll go to shit without us, so call it a necessary evil.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Huh? The hell's that supposed to mean?

All right then, if you're not gonna
give it back, I'll just beat it outta you!

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_boss_.TB: Dammit. I guess this is it...

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
I'll bet you've had enough.
Just gimme back the money, and we're good.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_boss_.TB:
Sorry, no can do. Even if I wanted to...
Heh, go ahead and kill me already.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Say what?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
About that thief. Do whatever you gotta do, even if that
means killin' the creep. Lowlifes like him aren't worth shit.

But if you do put him six feet under, just empty his pockets first, all right?
Again, I'll leave all that up to you. See ya.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_son_s.TB:
Wait! Don't kill our boss!
Not him! He's my dad, all right!

Dad's been going around giving money and food to the people
this town forgot. The rich just get richer here, so what's
a few yen to them? Should be a drop in the bucket.

You said you were from the Yashima Family, right?
We'll give back the money we stole... So please, just let us go.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
So the rumors were true. It really was Nezumi Kozo
and his gang. Thieves, sure, but chivalrous ones at that.
That explains why you only stole food.
What'll it be, Daito-san?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: All right.

So long as the money from the Family gets returned, we're square.
I'm not interested in anything else.

Besides, if we'd been smart, we might
not have gotten it stolen in the first place.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: ...Why are you looking at me?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
If you take this thing too far, you might get killed
for real one day. Might wanna lay low for awhile.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_boss_.TB:
I... Thank you so much...
I'll repay you someday, I swear it.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_son_s.TB:
This here's all we took from the Yashima Family.
Again, we're really sorry.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Great, now I can report back to the Family.
Appreciate all your help.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Please. Not every day you get to see something so touching.
Haha. Plus now I've got a new story to tell my regulars.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Yeah, just make sure you get your story straight.
Can't have you giving people the wrong idea.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: Not to worry. I'll paint you out as a man among men.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: That's not really what I meant...
Anyway, I should get back to the Family.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB:
Yes, I ought to get back to the shop. Stop by as
a customer next time. I'll make it worth the visit.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (All right, time to report back.)
C'mon, you really think I'm gonna buy that?

Your reasons might've been noble, but your actions said otherwise.
If I keep giving into that, I'll end up in the ground one day.

The world's got no room for the soft-hearted.
This was nothing personal.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_son_s.TB:
How... How could you...
He was my dad, you bastard!

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Consider this payback for what you did. I'll let you
off the hook, in exchange for your boss's life.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-thief_son_s.TB:
Son of a bitch, I won't forget this.
I WILL get my revenge, you hear me.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: So then... This is how Nezumi Kozo meets his end.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
We all have to own up to the choices we make.
Whether it's right or wrong, that depends on who you ask.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: I suppose so.

Without their boss, the group will collapse,
and things'll likely be quiet from now on.
That should put the customer's minds at ease.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: ...Right.
Well then, I'd better head back.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-cafe_master.TB: And I to my shop. Farewell.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (...I should report back to the Yashima Family.)

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
I'm counting on you to take care of this thief thing quick.
Try starting with the café owner.

I'm counting on you to take care of this thief thing quick.
I see you got the owner with you, so that's progress,
but don't make a big scene out of it, yeah?

I'm counting on you to take care of this thief thing quick.
Try starting with the café owner.

I'm counting on you to take care of this thief thing quick.
You think now's really the time to be chasin' tail?

There you are, Daito.
So then, how'd it go?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
I got it back like you asked.
This is all of it, right?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
Yep, everything's accounted for.
You work fast. Good shit, kid.
Oh, yeah. Here's your allowance.
Don't go blabbing this to Aniki, eh?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB: Hey. Just what are you two being all sneaky about?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
Oh, boss! Nah, I was just giving Daito
a little extra encouragement, is all! Right?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Huh?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB:
Heh. Well, ain't that nice.
Now let me encourage you to put money back in the safe.
There won't be a next time, got it?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Looks like he was onto you.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB: Yo, Daito. Heard you offed that thief and got the money back.

Not bad man. I'm seeing you in a whole new light.
Never thought you'd actually kill the guy.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Weren't you the one who said I should?

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB:
Hey, I said I'd leave it up to you.
But so what if you killed him? I ain't complaining.

An order from above is absolute. It's a brutal world out
there, and the only way to come out on top is to use
whatever tricks you can. Take my word for it.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: ...Here's the money.

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-yashima_sha.TB: Yep, it's all here and accounted for.

Oh, yeah. And here's your allowance.
There's a little extra on top, too.

Well, I'll see you around. Next time, we oughta
team up for an even bigger job. Hahaha!

talk\\text\\crw_side01.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (I ought to head back to town...)

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB:
Rumor has it that there's some homicidal maniac loose on the streets around here.
Heard anything about it?

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: No, not at all. You sure there's someone crazy like that around here?

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB:
Yep, and they seem to come out at night.
I've actually seen tons of corpses scattered around by morning.

We've gotten less customers thanks to that,
and now our business is taking a hit.

That's where you come in.
You seem pretty sure about your skills.

I want you to pummel this murderer. Since you're a new face around here,
you'll probably stick out and be the perfect target for him.

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: So you want me to act as bait?

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB: If we're not mincing words, yeah.

If you get it done, I'll give you a little token of my appreciation.
And I'll even put in a good word to the boss for ya.
So... You up to beating down that killer?

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: All right, fine. I'll give it a shot.

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB:
Well aren't you dependable?
Okay, give it a go once the sun sets.

Hey, I won't force it on ya.
Come back if you change your mind.

The killer's likely to show up somewhere around here.
Anyway, I'm counting on ya.

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Phew. Didn't think he was actually real.
That was close.

talk\\text\\crw_side02.lxtxt-yashima_kas.TB:
Nice, you actually pulled it off.
So this guy's the killer, huh?

Heh. Well look at you.
Here's your reward—you've earned it.

Okay, see ya later.
I'll call on you again if something else comes up.

talk\\text\\crw_side03.lxtxt-daito_shate.TB: Aniki! Who do you wanna fight?
No problem! Stop by any time you'd like!

That was great!
Let me know if you want to fight again.

talk\\text\\crw_side04.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
The owner from the café told me to find you. He said there'd be
something good in it for me if I asked for your help.

talk\\text\\crw_side04.lxtxt-urabuki_sid.TB:
Oh? That means you've earned his trust then.
That's impressive for someone so young.
You might just make a good trading partner yet.

From now on, come to me if you are in trouble and need something.
I can offer you goods that may help you with your problem.
Here's something to commemorate our new partnership.

Of course. Think of it as a give-and-take. Don't worry—
I'll require your services sooner or later.
I'll send word once I procure some choice goods. Come back then.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Hey, mister! Wanna spend some time with me?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (I can't think of anything good to say back.)

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: What's wrong, mister?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: You'll show me a good time, right?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Of course I will.
But before that... How long do you want to enjoy yourself with me for?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Let's see...

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: That long!? Wow, what a man! Wonderful! ♥
Hehe, thank you.

Hmm. I see... I guess you'll just have to come back
and let me show you a good time then.
My name is Shizue. How about yours, mister?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: It's Daito Makoto.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: My, what a nice name!
Well then, Daito-san. Where will you take me?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (I can't think of a good location.)

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: What's wrong?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Let's go to a café. I know a good one.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Sounds good to me!
I've been wanting to go to a quiet place and relax.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Do you not like lively places?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB:
It's not that. I just had my hair done, so I didn't want to
mess it up by entertaining outside.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Makes sense.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-system_side.TB:
○: Nice weather today.
△: Your hair looks nice.
✕:Maybe I should buy something nice for you to wear in your hair next time.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Anyway, nice weather we're having today.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Huh? Oh, yeah. It is.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: (Well that killed the mood.)
Your hair looks nice.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Really? You're just saying that. But it means a lot, so thank you.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Maybe I should buy you something nice that you
can wear in your hair next time.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Oh, you will? Does that mean you'll pick something out for me?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
Sure. With hair that beautiful, it'd be a crime not to have
a pretty hair accessory to go with it.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Thanks. ♥ I can't wait!

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Let's relax here.
Have you lived in this town for long?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB:
Yeah. But I have a dream that I want to make a reality no matter
what, so I'm actually thinking of leaving this town.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: A dream?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Yup. Promise you won't laugh?

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Of course I won't.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB:
One day, I want to go to Tokyo and become a famous singer.
But to do that, I have to save up all the money I can.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
You have such a nice voice. In fact, if it's all right with you,
I'd love to hear you sing some time.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Thank you. If there comes a day we meet again, I'll sing for you.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB: Great, I'm looking forward to it. I hope your dream comes true.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB: Yeah...

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-daito_side_.TB:
It's great that you have a dream like that. I hope
you'll be able to achieve it some day.

talk\\text\\crw_side05.lxtxt-shizue_side.TB:
Yeah. I still don't have enough money yet—not even close.
So I don't know when I'll be able to make my dream come true.
